==English==
===Etymology===
Arabic [[غازي]], active participle of [[غزا]] ‘raid’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'gɑ:zi/

===Noun===
'''ghazi'''
# a [[hero]] or [[champion]], especially as a [[Muslim]] against non-Muslims; often used as a title
#:*'''2001''': On a particularly joyous day of the festivities, below Our Sultan’s loge overlooking the Hippodrome, a division of impoverished frontier '''ghazis''' appeared in tattered clothes. — Orhan Pamuk, ''My Name Is Red'', tr. Erdağ M Göknar